	<td>
		<p>
			<font face="verdana" size="3" color="#9f3215"><b>    Lord Grimrot's Alena</b></font>
			<br>
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="#9f3215">
			<b><a href="mailto: ">Bathory</a> | 
                        12/17/1999 11:48:25 AM</b></font></p>
			
			<p>
			<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">Visit Lord Grimrot, who really isn't such a bad fellow once you get to know him. He will tell you a sorrowful tale about his lost beloved, Alena. It seems that he created Alena himself with beautifully decaying flesh and bone, to be his companion. Once while Grimrot was on a walkabout, Alena took it into her pretty head to wander off. Lord Grimrot believes that she may be headed to where he found her, or her parts anyway, in MIstmoore Castle on Faywer. Find Alena, &quot;stop&quot; her (which I take as kill) and bring her remains back to Lord Grimrot so that he may reanimate his beloved.
	<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
			</p>
	</td>
